19 To’n 21  (19 To 21)

ਆਦਮੀ ਹਰੇਕ ਰਿਹਾ ਉੱਤੇ ਨੂੰ ਹੀ ਵੇਖ, 
ਸੋਚੇ ਉੰਨੀ ਤੇ ਖਲੋਤਾ ਕਿੱਦਾ ਟੱਪ ਜਾਵਾਂ ਇੱਕੀ। 
ਏਸ ਤੋਂ ਅਗਾਹਾਂ ਤਾਂ ‘ਫ਼ੇ ਗੁੰਮ ਜਾਣ ਰਾਹਾਂ। 
ਯਾਰਾ ਫੇਰ ਨਈਓਂ ਤੋੜ ਹੁੰਦੀ ਕਾਗ਼ਜ਼ੀ ਕੁੜਿੱਕੀ। 
Everybody is only looking at what’s above,
Thinking so much to go above & higher !
Further than the beautiful ways of living generally get lost & that trap of money can never be broken !

ਤੇਤੀ ਸੰਗ ਜੋੜ ਦਿੱਤੇ ਦੇਵਤੇ ਕਰੋੜ 
ਖ਼ੌਰੇ ਰਹਿੰਦੇ ਨੇ ਜ਼ਮੀਨਾਂ ਤੇ ਜਾਂ ਰਹਿੰਦੇ ਆਸਮਾਨਾਂ ਤੇ। 
ਰੱਬ ਦੇ ਨੇ ਭਾਣੇ ਨਾ ਮੈਂ ਦੇਖੇ ਸੁਣੇ ਜਾਏ, 
ਜਿਹੜੇ ਥੋੜ੍ਹੇ ਕੁ ਸਿਆਣੇ ਸੀਗੇ ਚੜ੍ਹ ਗਏ ਚਟਾਨਾਂ ਤੇ। 
ਇਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਹੀ ਖ਼ਿਆਲਾਂ ਵਿੱਚ ਸਮੇਂ ਦੀਆਂ ਚਾਲਾਂ ਵਿੱਚ, 
ਸਾਰੀ-ਸਾਰੀ ਰਾਤ ਵੇਖਾਂ ਚੰਨ ਵਾਲ਼ੀ ਟਿੱਕੀ। 
Number 33 is related to mythology of the 330 million Deities ; who knows if they live on planet earth or in skies !
It’s the mystery of the Almighty; I have no idea, few who know, left the world & meditating in the mountains !
In these very thoughts, through the rhythms of time, I spend entire nights gazing at the moon’s little spot.

ਚੱਕਰ ਚੌਰਾਸੀ ਲੱਖ ਜੂਨ ਦੀ ਖ਼ਲਾਸੀ, 
ਕਿੱਦਾਂ ਹੁੰਦੀ ਕਿੰਨੇ ਯੁੱਗ ਲੱਗੇ ਚੱਕਰ ਮੁਕਾਉਣ ਨੂੰ। 
ਆਬਰੂ ਦਾ ਮਹਿਲ ਸਾਰੀ ਜ਼ਿੰਦਗੀ ਬਣਾਇਆ ਜਾਂਦਾ, 
ਇੱਕ ਪਲ ਲਗਦਾ ਏ ਓਹੀ ਮਹਿਲ ਢਾਉਣ ਨੂੰ। 
ਤਾਂ ਹੀ ਤਾਂ ਮੈਂ ਯਾਰ ਤੈਨੂੰ ਕਹਿੰਨਾਂ ਬਾਰ-ਬਾਰ, 
ਕਿ ਤੂੰ ਜਾਣੀਂ ਨਾ ਬੇਕਾਰ ਇਹ ਕੋਈ ਵੀ ਗੱਲ ਨਿੱਕੀ। 
Round & round in the cycle of eighty-four lakhs of births, how many ages it takes to complete the circle!
The palace of honor is built over a lifetime,
Yet it takes only a moment to destroy that same palace.
That is why, my friend, I tell you again & again:
Do not think any of these matters are trivial !

ਗੇੜ ਜੋ ਨੜਿੰਨਵੇਂ ਦਾ ਚੈਨ-ਸੁੱਖ ਵਿੰਨਵੇਂ ਦਾ। 
ਹਾਲ ਕੀ ਓ ਪੁੱਛਦੇ ਜੋ ਫ਼ਸੇ ਓਹੀ ਜਾਣਦੇ। 
ਏਸ ਗੇੜ ਪਿੱਛੋਂ ਤਾਂ ਹਾਲਾਤ ਐਸੇ ਹੁੰਦੇ, 
ਬੰਦੇ ਸ਼ੀਸ਼ੇ ਵਿੱਚ ਦੇਖ ਕੇ ਨਾ ਖ਼ੁਦ ਨੂੰ ਨਾ ਪਛਾਣਦੇ। 
ਆਜੋ ਰਲ਼ ਗਾਈਏ “ਸਰਤਾਜ” ਮਿੱਠੇ ਪਾਈਏ, 
ਤੇ ਸਵਾਦਲੀ ਬਣਾਈਏ ਏਹੋ ਜ਼ਿੰਦਗਾਨੀ  ਫ਼ਿੱਕੀ।
Reflections on Life
The vicissitude of the number of 99 which generally destroy the peace ; Only those trapped truly know their state !
From this knot of life come such circumstances
That one sees oneself in a mirror and hardly recognizes.
So Sartaaj says ; let’s sing together by putting some sweetness & make this life flavorful, not bland !

Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/SatinderSartaaj

Enjoy & Stay Connected With us !

snippet.title: Lee Cronin’s The Mummy | Official Teaser
snippet.description:
Some things are meant to stay buried. #LeeCroninsTheMummy only in theaters April 17, 2026.

Hot off the record-setting resurrection of EVIL DEAD RISE, writer/director Lee Cronin turns to one of the most iconic horror stories of all time with an audacious and twisted retelling: LEE CRONIN’S THE MUMMY. 

The young daughter of a journalist disappears into the desert without a trace—eight years later, the broken family is shocked when she is returned to them, as what should be a joyful reunion turns into a living nightmare.

The film stars Jack Reynor, Laia Costa, May Calamawy, Natalie Grace, with Veronica Falcón. The film is written and directed by Cronin, and produced by James Wan, Jason Blum and John Keville. The executive producers are Michael Clear, Judson Scott, Macdara Kelleher and Lee Cronin. 

Cronin is supported behind the camera by a team of sterling film artisans, including director of photography Dave Garbett, production designer Nick Bassett, editor Bryan Shaw, costume designer Joanna Eatwell, music by Stephen McKeon and casting by Terri Taylor and Sarah Domeier Lindo. 

New Line Cinema, Atomic Monster and Blumhouse Present, A Wicked/Good Production, A Lee Cronin Film: LEE CRONIN’S THE MUMMY. The film will be distributed worldwide by Warner Bros. Pictures, only in theaters and IMAX in North America on April 17, 2026, and internationally beginning 15 April 2026.

snippet.title: Nothing
snippet.description:
nothin
nothin
is enough
nothin 
nothin
is enough

you could tear out your heart
you could rip out your mind
and all of the blood
that poured out
still wouldn't be
enough

people that you know are strange
time carves lines into their faces
years just drag you down the road
and you can't change the way it seems
like punching demons in your dreams
revenge is like a rolling stone
it always finds it way back home

something
something
don't add up
something
something
don't add up

crazy men with bloodshot eyes
shoot their rockets in the sky
drunk with power high with rage
and all the treasure all the blood
all the gold and all the guts
would never make a bit of change
new men in the same old cage
